I think a skill shot heals/shields would be a "mager" {{sticker:slayer-jinx-wink}}  benefit. Allowing for accurate players to heal their teammates from 800 - 1200 range.
old {{champion:81}} 
{{champion:99}} 

Is there range of use. All heals and shields (except Lux' shield) happen at close range, by making it a skill shot, you can save a teammate from a much safer distance as with Lux' shield, {{champion:16}} ult, {{champion:412}} lantern, {{champion:432}} shrine and old {{champion:81}} heal.

Pretty sure they would be frustration factories... part of the reason I never liked upgrading swindler's orb into orb of trust during the Bilgewater event {{sticker:zombie-nunu-bummed}} 
unless I had multiple slow/dashless champs on my team.

-LostFr0st
